Tomopaguroides valdiviae
(
Balss, 1911
)

(
Figs 1
; 
2
)

Shield (
Fig. 2A
) somewhat vaulted; considerably longer than broad; anterior margin between rostrum and lateral projections concave; anterolateral margins sloping; posterior margin roundly truncate; dorsal surface well calcified, slightly rugose and pitted but glabrous. Rostrum acutely triangular, produced beyond bases of ocular acicles but often not beyond level of lateral projections, terminating with spinule or spine. Lateral projections well developed, acute, subacute or blunt, each with prominent marginal or submarginal spine, occasionally with both marginal and submarginal pair of spines.

